Business Description: Thrivent Financial for Lutherans (Thrivent Financial) provides a wide range of annuities, insurance, mutual funds and other investments products and services. It also offers education funding options, business continuation plans, retirement products, charitable giving options and estate strategies.  Thrivent offers its products and services to individuals and families, businesses, churches and non-profit organizations, advisors and independent producers, and members.  As on December 31, 2021, it had 1,256 million members and US$189 billion in assets under management.  Thrivent Financial provides annuities, insurance, and investment products.  The annuity products include deferred fixed annuities, immediate fixed annuities, fixed indexed annuities, deferred income annuities, immediate variable annuities and variable annuities. Deferred fixed annuities pay interest at a fixed rate. Immediate annuities are the annuities, which provide predictable source of income immediately. Fixed indexed annuities provide growth potential while protecting assets from losses. Deferred income annuities create guaranteed fixed income. Immediate variable annuities offer income immediately and continue rest of life based on the performance of the stock and bond investments. The variable annuities performance depends on investment options and hence the value fluctuates.  Thrivent Financial’s insurance products include life insurance, disability income insurance, long-term care insurance, and Medicare supplement insurance. The company invests in mutual funds, interval funds, exchange-traded funds (ETFs), Closed-end funds, stocks, taxable and tax-exempt bonds, preferred stocks and convertible securities.  It offers mutual funds with a wide range of investment options, such as Thrivent asset allocation funds, Thrivent equity funds, Thrivent income plus funds, Thrivent fixed income funds. Thrivent asset allocation funds include Aggressive Allocation Fund, Moderately Aggressive Allocation Fund, Moderate Allocation Fund and Moderately Conservative Allocation Fund.   Thrivent Equity Funds comprises low volatility equity fund, large cap stock fund, large cap value fund, large cap growth fund, mid cap stock fund, small cap stock fund, small cap growth fund, partner worldwide allocation fund, and partner emerging markets equity fund.  Its Thrivent income plus funds include Balanced Income Plus Fund, Diversified Income Plus Fund, Opportunity Income Plus Fund.  Its Thrivent Fixed Income Funds comprises multidimensional income fund, high yield fund, high income municipal bond fund, income fund, municipal bond fund, government bond fund, limited maturity bond fund, and money market fund.  Thrivent Financial also offers personal service and professional guidance services to its shareholders through its wholly owned subsidiary, Thrivent Asset Management. Thrivent Financial also operates a church loan program, which provides finance for the construction of new churches and school expansions and the maintenance of existing ones. It also offers individual retirement account that includes a variety of investments such as mutual funds, annuities, stock and bonds.

Business Description: East Central Energy (ECE) provides electric service to farms, homes, and businesses in east central Minnesota and northwestern Wisconsin. ECE procures wholesale electricity from Great River Energy (GRE), a not-for-profit electric cooperative, which provides wholesale electric service to its member cooperatives. GRE generates electricity and transmits it from power plants to ECE substations for distribution through local lines to consumer-members.  The company distributes electricity to residential, commercial and industrial, irrigation, and public street and highway lighting customers. As of December 31, 2021, ECE served 62,462 members through 8,434 miles of electricity lines. In FY2021, it sold 936.7 million kilowatt hours (kWh) of electricity. In FY2021, the company generated revenue from different sources,which include major contribution from residential customers with 62.73% followed by 22.28% commercial and industrial customers (1000 KVA or less), 6.66% commercial and industrial (over 1000 KVA), 4.59% residential seasonal customers, 1.99% of capital credits, 1.03% other revenue, 0.41% irrigation and 0.31% public street and highway lighting. ECE also owns a stake in Milaca Local Link, which provides high-speed Internet, telecommunications, and cable television services in the city of Milaca, Minnesota. Through Northland Connect Broadband, the company offers ViaSat satellite speed Internet services. ECE provides energy conservation and management services and energy-saving tips to consumer-members. The company also offers rebates on motors and drives, lighting systems, and heating, ventilation, and air conditioning systems. It assists customers in purchasing energy-efficient systems. Through the Renewable Energy program, ECE along with Great River Energy and Haubenschild Farms Dairy Inc supports the development of renewable energy.
